    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single deficiency — Test conditions achieving Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3 — is considered acceptable given the strong aggregate performance across all remaining factors and the consistency of results across two independent laboratories. The overall credibility of the simulation evidence is assessed as Medium, sufficient to support the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
